<item>
            <title>[TIKA-194] Support java regular expressions in glob pattern spec for mime repo</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-194</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the mime repo does not support java regular expressions as specifications for glob patterns. It would be nice to support this, e.g., with a flag such as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;glob pattern=&quot;\d&lt;/p&gt;
{4}
&lt;p&gt;*.txt&quot; isregex=&quot;true&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When specified &lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt; set to &quot;true&quot;, the flag would indicate that a glob pattern is to be interpreted as a java regular expression, rather than a std freedesktop.org mime glob pattern.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch forthcoming.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;indep. of env.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
